{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29cd6d70-53e3-4fd8-a8f5-73675a02cbd9","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — a file can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** it. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFix: reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_uzvPlfTWygh8pJ5r9gJiAu","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8750d636003e4d769eac11be467d9ab1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8750d636003e4d769eac11be467d9ab1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"0f753b47-66ee-4892-bde3-c5fe9250acf2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order in the `.fsproj` matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs (depends on Domain.fs)\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nServices.fs opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but Domain.fs is listed after it. The fix is to put Domain.fs first.","outputTokens":411,"requestId":"5C00:1CFDE0:1E9627B:2267F33:6A07C8B8"},"id":"9a34b5db-6bf1-456a-a115-255b14e5d861","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:30:39.753Z","parentId":"a2cbe612-b977-4452-88a9-9e90e7be0aa1"}
